---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="YieldRadar Documentation — Methodology & Architecture" description="Full technical documentation for YieldRadar: 10-factor risk scoring formula, data pipeline architecture, GoPlus security integration, and risk tier definitions.">

<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://yieldradar.io" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Docs", "item": "https://yieldradar.io/docs" }
  ]
})} />

<section style="padding: 3rem 0 1rem;">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h1>Documentation</h1>
    <p class="lead">How YieldRadar scores risk, filters pools, and delivers alerts. Everything documented — no black box.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-inner docs-section">
  <h2>Tech stack</h2>
  <dl class="docs-deflist">
    <dt>Runtime</dt>
    <dd>Node.js 24 with TypeScript (ESM, strict mode)</dd>
    <dt>Bot framework</dt>
    <dd>Grammy with conversations plugin</dd>
    <dt>Database</dt>
    <dd>SQLite (better-sqlite3, WAL mode)</dd>
    <dt>Testing</dt>
    <dd>Vitest (738 tests)</dd>
    <dt>Deployment</dt>
    <dd>Docker, multi-stage build</dd>
  </dl>
</section>

<section class="section-inner docs-section">
  <h2>Architecture</h2>
  <div class="pipeline">
    <div class="pipeline-step">
      <div class="step-icon">
