  <p class="docs-note">Data flows in one direction. The bot polls DeFiLlama every 5 minutes, filters down to ~2,000 eligible pools, scores each one on ten risk factors, and pushes matches to subscribed users.</p>
</section>

<section class="section-inner docs-section">
  <h2>Data pipeline — filtering in detail</h2>
  <p>The raw DeFiLlama dataset contains ~15,000 pools across all supported chains. Not all of them are worth analyzing. Here's the filtering pipeline:</p>

  <div class="docs-steps">
    <div class="docs-step">
      <span class="docs-step-num">1</span>
      <div>
        <h3>Raw data</h3>
        <p><strong>~15,000 pools</strong> fetched from DeFiLlama every 5 minutes — APY, TVL, 7d APY change, chain, protocol, and token addresses across all supported chains.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-step">
      <span class="docs-step-num">2</span>
      <div>
        <h3>Hard filters</h3>
        <p>Pools must meet all of these criteria to proceed:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>TVL ≥ $500K</strong> — removes micro-liquidity pools</li>
          <li><strong>Outlier == false</strong> — DeFiLlama's own outlier flag filters anomalous data</li>
          <li><strong>APY > 0</strong> — removes pools with zero or negative yield</li>
          <li><strong>7d change > -50%</strong> — removes collapsing pools</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-step">
      <span class="docs-step-num">3</span>
      <div>
        <h3>After filtering</h3>
        <p><strong>~2,000 eligible pools</strong> remain — roughly 13% of the raw dataset. These are the pools that enter the risk scoring engine.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-step">
      <span class="docs-step-num">4</span>
      <div>
        <h3>Scoring</h3>
        <p>Each eligible pool receives a <strong>10-factor composite score</strong> (0–100). See the risk scoring model below for the formula.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-step">
      <span class="docs-step-num">5</span>
      <div>
        <h3>Alert delivery</h3>
        <p>Scored pools are matched against each user's preferences (chain, risk tolerance, minimum TVL, APY range) and pushed as individual alerts or included in the daily digest.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-inner docs-section">
  <h2>Risk scoring model</h2>
  <p>Each pool receives a composite score based on ten weighted factors. The score is normalized to a 0–100 scale where higher is safer.</p>

      <h3>The formula</h3>
      <div class="docs-formula">
    <p><code>rawScore = APY / max(sigma, 0.01)</code></p>
    <p class="formula-note">where <strong>APY</strong> is the Annual Percentage Yield (including compounding) and <strong>sigma</strong> is the standard deviation of APY over available snapshots — measures yield stability. <a href="/learn#apy-vs-apr" style="color: var(--color-primary); font-size: 0.85rem;">Learn more about APY →</a></p>

    <p><code>riskAdjustedScore = rawScore × TVL_multiplier × trend_multiplier × IL_multiplier × maturity_multiplier</code></p>
    <p class="formula-note">four core multipliers adjust the raw score up or down based on pool-specific risk factors</p>

    <p><code>finalScore = riskAdjustedScore × securityMultiplier × protocolTierMultiplier × addressSecurityMultiplier × rugpullMultiplier × protocolRiskMultiplier × emissionMultiplier</code></p>
    <p class="formula-note">six additional GoPlus, protocol, and emission factors — each as a weighted multiplier (0.0–1.0)</p>

    <p><code>normalizedScore = logPercentile(riskAdjustedScore, batchP5, batchP95)</code></p>
    <p class="formula-note">log-percentile normalization — transforms scores through log-space and maps P5→0, P95→100 to handle power-law yield distributions</p>
  </div>

  <h3>Worked example</h3>
  <div class="docs-example">
    <p><strong>Pool:</strong> Aave — USDC on Ethereum</p>
    <ul>
      <li>APY: 12% (stable, sigma = 0.3)</li>
      <li>TVL: $50M (large, deep liquidity)</li>
      <li>7d trend: slightly positive</li>
      <li>Impermanent loss: none (single-asset lending)</li>
      <li>Maturity: 60+ days of snapshots</li>
      <li>GoPlus token security score: 95/100</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Calculation:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li><code>rawScore = 12 / max(0.3, 0.01) = 40.0</code></li>
      <li>TVL multiplier: 1.0 (large cap)</li>
      <li>Trend multiplier: 1.0 (stable)</li>
      <li>IL multiplier: 1.0 (no IL for lending)</li>
      <li>Maturity multiplier: 1.0 (established)</li>
      <li>Security multiplier: 0.95 (GoPlus score)</li>
      <li><code>riskAdjustedScore = 40.0 × 1.0 × 1.0 × 1.0 × 1.0 × 0.95 = 38.0</code></li>
      <li><strong>Normalized score: ~85 (Safe Yield tier)</strong></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Factor breakdown</h3>
  <div class="docs-table-wrap">
    <table class="docs-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Factor</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Source</th>
          <th>What it measures</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>APY / volatility</td>
          <td>Base formula</td>
          <td>DeFiLlama</td>
          <td>Yield adjusted for stability — high APY with high volatility scores lower</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><a href="/learn#what-is-tvl" style="color: var(--color-primary);">TVL</a> quality</td>
          <td>Multiplier</td>
          <td>DeFiLlama</td>
          <td>Deeper liquidity = more scrutiny, harder to manipulate</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>7-day trend</td>
          <td>Multiplier</td>
          <td>DeFiLlama</td>
          <td>Rising or stable APY is positive; sharp drops are penalized</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><a href="/learn#impermanent-loss" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Impermanent loss</a></td>
          <td>0.5x penalty</td>
          <td>DeFiLlama</td>
          <td>LP pairs with volatile tokens face IL risk</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Pool maturity</td>
          <td>Multiplier</td>
          <td>Internal (snapshot count)</td>
          <td>Newer pools get lower scores — insufficient track record</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Token security</td>
          <td>0.0–1.0 multiplier</td>
          <td>GoPlus API</td>
          <td>Honeypot detection, malicious contract scan, token tax analysis (15 conditions)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Address security</td>
          <td>0.0–1.0 multiplier</td>
          <td>GoPlus API</td>
          <td>Malicious address flags — sanctions, phishing, blacklist, honeypot creator</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Rugpull detection</td>
          <td>0.0–1.0 multiplier</td>
          <td>GoPlus API</td>
          <td>Rugpull risk scoring based on contract patterns and holder distribution</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Protocol tier</td>
          <td>Tier classification</td>
          <td>DeFiLlama protocols</td>
          <td>Audit status, protocol age, and category factor into risk via tier multiplier</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Emission decay</td>
          <td>0.0–1.0 multiplier</td>
          <td>Internal (APY history)</td>
          <td>Detects emission-based yields and penalizes decaying reward structures</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-inner docs-section">
  <h2>Risk tiers</h2>
  <p>Every scored pool is classified into one of four tiers:</p>

  <dl class="tiers">
    <div class="tier tier-safe">
      <dt><span class="tier-badge">Safe Yield</span> <span class="tier-range">Score 75–100</span></dt>
      <dd>Low volatility, high TVL, established protocols with positive or stable trends. These are typically blue-chip lending pools (Aave, Compound) or major DEX stablecoin pairs with consistent, revenue-based yields. The boring ones that make money reliably.</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="tier tier-watch">
      <dt><span class="tier-badge">Watch</span> <span class="tier-range">Score 50–74</span></dt>
      <dd>Decent fundamentals but with moderate risk factors. May have some APY volatility, slightly lower TVL, or newer protocols without a long track record. Worth monitoring — not blindly entering. Many good opportunities live here, but require attention.</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="tier tier-speculative">
      <dt><span class="tier-badge">Speculative</span> <span class="tier-range">Score 25–49</span></dt>
      <dd>High APY but elevated risk across multiple factors. Often newer protocols, volatile yields, lower TVL, or token pairs with impermanent loss risk. Can be profitable for experienced users who understand the risks and actively manage positions.</dd>
    </div>
    <div class="tier tier-danger">
      <dt><span class="tier-badge">Danger Zone</span> <span class="tier-range">Score 0–24</span></dt>
      <dd>Multiple red flags: honeypot patterns detected by GoPlus, malicious contract signatures, extremely low TVL, extreme APY volatility, or negative trends. We flag these so you can avoid them — not because they can't pay out, but because the risk of total loss is significant.</dd>
    </div>
  </dl>
</section>

<section class="section-inner docs-section">
  <h2>API sources</h2>
  <dl class="docs-deflist">
    <dt>DeFiLlama</dt>
    <dd>Primary data source — pool data, APY, TVL, 7d APY change, protocol metadata, audit status, and chain information. Polled every 5 minutes.</dd>
    <dt>GoPlus Security</dt>
    <dd>Multi-endpoint security analysis — token security (honeypot, malicious contracts, transfer tax), address security (sanctions, phishing), rugpull detection, approval security, and phishing site detection. Each endpoint contributes a weighted multiplier to the composite risk score.</dd>
  </dl>
</section>

<section class="section-inner docs-section" style="padding-bottom: 3rem;">
  <div style="background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; text-align: center;">
    <h2>Try it yourself</h2>
    <p style="margin: 1rem 0; color: var(--color-text-muted);">See the risk scoring in action — every alert includes the full score breakdown. <a href="https://t.me/YieldRadar_io_bot" style="color: var(--color-primary); text-decoration: underline;">Start free on Telegram</a>.</p>
    <a href="https://t.me/YieldRadar_io_bot" class="cta-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open in Telegram →</a>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

